data.value: Caused by bacterial infection with the bacterium Chlamydia trachomatis. According to research, it is known as a public health problem in 37 countries, affecting 158+ million people globally and those that live in developing countries are the most at risk of contracting it. It can easily be contracted via absorption from physical contact with those that are infected or via objects. The bacterium causes blindness by drying the cornea of the eye causing eyelashes to turn inwards, scratching the surface of the eye.
